# 🏦 INTELLI-CREDIT — TEAM MODULARIZATION PLAN
**Hackathon:** IIT Hyderabad | **Deadline:** 10 March 2026 (EOD)
**Goal:** Each person builds their module independently. On Day 5 and Day 8 we integrate.

---

## 🗂️ Module Overview

| Module | Owner | Days | Deliverable |
|--------|-------|------|-------------|
| **M1 — Document Intelligence** | Person 1 | Days 1–6 | `DocumentReport` dict |
| **M2 — Research Agent** | Person 2 | Days 1–6 | `ResearchReport` dict |
| **M3 — Scoring & Explainability** | Person 3 | Days 1–6 | `ScoringResult` dict + CAM doc |
| **M4 — Frontend Portal** | Person 4 | Days 1–8 | Streamlit app (`app.py`) |

> **Rule:** Every module consumes and produces a **Python dict with a fixed schema** (the contract below). If your upstream module isn't ready, use the mock data provided. This means you are NEVER blocked.

---

## 📦 The Data Contracts (How Modules Talk to Each Other)

### Contract 1 — `DocumentReport` (output of M1, input to M3 & M4)

```python
document_report = {
    "company_name": "Apex Textiles Pvt Ltd",
    "gstin": "27AAPCA1234F1Z5",
    "financials": {
        "revenue_cr": 42.5,            # ₹ Crore
        "ebitda_cr": 6.1,
        "net_profit_cr": 2.3,
        "total_assets_cr": 38.0,
        "total_liabilities_cr": 24.0,
        "net_worth_cr": 14.0,
        "dscr": 0.89,                  # Debt Service Coverage Ratio
        "current_ratio": 1.1,
        "debt_to_equity": 1.71,
        "interest_coverage": 2.4,
    },
    "gst_analysis": {
        "mismatch_pct": 18.2,          # GSTR-3B vs GSTR-2A gap
        "mismatch_flag": "RED",        # RED / YELLOW / GREEN
        "circular_trading_flag": True,
        "revenue_inflation_flag": False,
        "gst_score": 12,               # out of 20
    },
    "bank_statement": {
        "avg_balance_cr": 1.8,
        "emi_outflow_monthly_cr": 0.42,
        "peak_balance_cr": 4.1,
        "regular_credits": True,
    },
    "extraction_confidence": 0.91,     # 0–1, flag if < 0.75
    "source_citations": {
        "revenue": "P&L Statement FY2024, Page 3, Line 7",
        "dscr":    "Balance Sheet FY2024, Page 8",
    }
}
```

---

### Contract 2 — `ResearchReport` (output of M2, input to M3 & M4)

```python
research_report = {
    "company_name": "Apex Textiles Pvt Ltd",
    "mca_data": {
        "cin": "U17200MH2010PTC123456",
        "status": "Active",
        "incorporation_date": "2010-04-15",
        "paid_up_capital_cr": 5.0,
        "directors": [
            {"name": "Ramesh Gupta", "din": "00123456", "other_companies": 3}
        ],
        "charges_outstanding": 2,      # existing bank liens on assets
        "struck_off_subsidiaries": 1,
    },
    "litigation": {
        "found": True,
        "cases": [
            {
                "case_id": "2023/NC/142",
                "court": "NCLT Mumbai",
                "parties": "Apex Textiles vs HDFC Bank",
                "status": "Dismissed",
                "source": "eCourts Portal, retrieved 01 Mar 2026"
            }
        ],
        "litigation_score_deduction": 15,
    },
    "news_sentiment": {
        "score": -0.3,                 # -1 (very bad) to +1 (very good)
        "headlines": [
            "Apex Textiles faces supplier payment delays — Economic Times, Jan 2026"
        ],
    },
    "sector_headwinds": "Textile sector NPA at 7.2% (RBI, Q3 FY2024)",
    "promoter_score": 9,               # out of 20
    "research_timestamp": "2026-03-01T14:32:00",
}
```

