## 👨‍💻 Module 1 — Document Intelligence (Person 1)

**What you own:** Everything from PDF/Excel upload → structured `DocumentReport`

### Files to Create
```
intelli-credit/
  modules/
    document_intelligence/
      pdf_ingestor.py       # text + OCR extraction
      financial_extractor.py # ratio computation
      gst_validator.py      # GSTR mismatch + circular trading
      bank_parser.py        # bank statement analysis
      document_pipeline.py  # orchestrates all above, returns DocumentReport
      mock_data.py          # DocumentReport mock for other teams
```

### Day-by-Day Tasks

| Day | Task |
|-----|------|
| 1–2 | Set up venv. Install: `pdfplumber camelot-py paddleocr pdf2image unstructured opencv-python pandas` |
| 3 | Build `PDFIngestor`: text extraction (pdfplumber) + OCR fallback (PaddleOCR) |
| 3 | Build `FinancialExtractor`: regex + LLM fallback to extract all fields in `DocumentReport.financials` |
| 4 | Build `GSTCrossValidator`: GSTR-3B vs GSTR-2A mismatch, circular trading, revenue inflation |
| 4 | Build `BankStatementParser`: CSV → categorized transaction summary |
| 5 | Write `mock_data.py` — a hardcoded `DocumentReport` dict for the demo company Apex Textiles |
| 5 | **Integration Day:** expose `run_pipeline(files: list) -> dict` and test with M3 team |
| 6 | Polish: confidence scoring, source citations, edge case handling |

### Key Interface
```python
# document_pipeline.py
def run_pipeline(uploaded_files: list[str], company_name: str) -> dict:
    """Returns DocumentReport dict"""
```

