## 📊 Module 3 — Scoring & Explainability + CAM Generator (Person 3)

**What you own:** `DocumentReport` + `ResearchReport` + officer notes → `ScoringResult` + `.docx` CAM

### Files to Create
```
intelli-credit/
  modules/
    scoring/
      scorecard_model.py     # 5-C weighted scoring logic
      explainability.py      # SHAP chart + LLM narrative generation
      loan_calculator.py     # recommended amount + rate
      ews_engine.py          # RBI EWS Level 1/2/3 classification
      cam_generator.py       # python-docx template → filled CAM Word doc
      scoring_pipeline.py    # single entry point → ScoringResult
      mock_data.py           # ScoringResult mock for M4 team
```

### Day-by-Day Tasks

| Day | Task |
|-----|------|
| 1–2 | Design the scoring weights on paper. Study SHAP library. |
| 3 | Build `ScorecardModel`: takes both reports, computes 5 component scores |
| 3 | Build `LoanTermsCalculator`: maps score → recommended sanction amount + rate |
| 4 | Build `ExplainabilityEngine`: SHAP waterfall dict + LLM narrative (Gemini API prompt) |
| 4 | Build `EWSEngine`: maps score signals to RBI EWS levels |
| 5 | Design CAM Word template using python-docx (structure from Section 4.7 of master plan) |
| 5 | Build `CAMGenerator`: populates template from all inputs, embeds matplotlib charts |
| 5 | Write `mock_data.py`. **Integration Day:** test pipeline with M1 + M2 mock data |
| 6 | Polish narrative quality. Test full CAM doc end-to-end. Set up MLflow local tracking. |

### Key Interface
```python
# scoring_pipeline.py
def run_scoring(
    document_report: dict,
    research_report: dict,
    officer_notes: str = ""
) -> dict:
    """Returns ScoringResult dict. Also writes CAM .docx to output/"""
```

### Qualitative Notes Parsing (Human-in-the-Loop)
```python
# In explainability.py
def parse_officer_notes(notes: str, current_score: dict) -> dict:
    """
    Send officer notes to Gemini. Extract risk signals.
    Return score delta and updated ScoringResult.
    Example: "Factory at 40% capacity" → extracts capacity_risk → deducts 8 pts
    """
```

