## 🖥️ Module 4 — Frontend Portal (Person 4)

**What you own:** The Streamlit UI — the face of the entire system

### Files to Create
```
intelli-credit/
  app.py                     # main Streamlit app
  components/
    upload_panel.py           # file uploader + company name input
    financial_panel.py        # extracted financial table (editable)
    gst_panel.py              # GST traffic lights + mismatch chart
    research_panel.py         # news cards + MCA + litigation display
    score_dashboard.py        # gauge chart + component breakdown
    decision_banner.py        # LEND / REJECT / CONDITIONS banner
    ews_panel.py              # Early Warning Signal cards
    cam_download.py           # Word + PDF download buttons
  demo_data/
    apex_textiles_document.json    # copy of M1 mock_data
    apex_textiles_research.json    # copy of M2 mock_data
    apex_textiles_scoring.json     # copy of M3 mock_data
```

### Day-by-Day Tasks

| Day | Task |
|-----|------|
| 1 | Set up Streamlit. Install all UI libs: `streamlit plotly matplotlib streamlit-extras` |
| 2 | Build `upload_panel.py`: multi-file uploader + company name + DEMO MODE toggle |
| 2–3 | Build `financial_panel.py`: editable table showing all values from `DocumentReport.financials` |
| 3 | Build `gst_panel.py`: traffic lights 🔴🟡🟢 + Matplotlib bar chart (declared vs actual GST) |
| 4 | Build `research_panel.py`: news headline cards + MCA summary + litigation table |
| 4 | Build `score_dashboard.py`: Plotly gauge chart (0–100) + horizontal bar chart of 5 components |
| 5 | Build `decision_banner.py`: big coloured banner (green/amber/red) + officer notes text area |
| 5 | **Integration Day:** wire real M1/M2/M3 pipeline calls into app.py (replace mock calls) |
| 6 | Build `ews_panel.py`: EWS signal cards with RBI level badges |
| 7–8 | Polish: custom CSS dark mode, progress bars during processing, stopwatch timer |
| 8 | Final end-to-end test. Record 3-minute demo video backup. |

### Key app.py Structure
```python
# app.py — skeleton
import streamlit as st
from modules.document_intelligence.document_pipeline import run_pipeline
from modules.research_agent.research_pipeline import run_research
from modules.scoring.scoring_pipeline import run_scoring

DEMO_MODE = st.sidebar.toggle("🎬 DEMO MODE", value=True)

if DEMO_MODE:
    doc_report  = load_json("demo_data/apex_textiles_document.json")
    res_report  = load_json("demo_data/apex_textiles_research.json")
    score_result = load_json("demo_data/apex_textiles_scoring.json")
else:
    # real pipeline calls
    uploaded = st.file_uploader(...)
    doc_report = run_pipeline(uploaded, company_name)
    res_report = run_research(company_name, promoter_names)
    score_result = run_scoring(doc_report, res_report, officer_notes)
```

